### Admin Report Management APIs

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7000/api/admin
@adminToken = YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Get all reports with pagination and filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports?PageIndex=1&PageSize=10&Status=Pending&Type=Bug&SearchKeyword=test
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 2. Get all reports (simple)
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports?PageIndex=1&PageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 3. Get a specific report by ID (Admin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 4. Update a report (Admin)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/reports/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "content": "Updated report content",
  "type": "Feature Request",
  "status": "In Progress",
  "notice": "We are working on this issue"
}

### 5. Update report status only (Admin)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/reports/1/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "status": "Resolved",
  "notice": "This issue has been fixed in the latest update"
}

### 6. Delete a report (Admin)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/reports/1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 7. Get reports by specific user
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/by-user/5
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 8. Get reports by status
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports?Status=Pending&PageIndex=1&PageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 9. Get reports by type
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports?Type=Bug&PageIndex=1&PageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 10. Search reports by keyword
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports?SearchKeyword=urgent&PageIndex=1&PageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
